# Frontend conventions

## Pages (App Router)

| Route | Role |
|-------|------|
| `/` | Landing |
| `/new` | Create event |
| `/e/[eventId]` | Guest respond |
| `/e/[eventId]/created` | Post-create links |
| `/e/[eventId]/manage` | Host dashboard |

## UX

- Mobile-first; touch-friendly controls
- Japanese labels: 出席可 / 出席不可, 回答期限, etc.
- Copy-link buttons on host-facing pages
- Confirm before deleting slots that have answers
- After deadline: read-only guest view with clear message

## Data fetching

- Prefer Server Components for initial load when no client interactivity needed
- Use `"use client"` for forms, matrix toggles, dialogs, clipboard API
- Store `responseToken` in cookie for guest re-edit

## Display

- Format dates: `yyyy/MM/dd` (date-only) or `yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm` (datetime), JST
- Host matrix: rows = guests, columns = slots, cells = ○/×
- Highlight best slot(s) by 出席可 count on manage page

## Components

Place shared UI in `src/components/` (e.g. `EventForm`, `SlotPicker`, `ResponseMatrix`, `CopyLinkButton`).

Do not add UI libraries beyond Tailwind unless already in the project.
